                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d74">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/3630: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Consul at Geneva (<persName corresp="#p_GPB1" type="to"
                        >Gilbert</persName>)</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-01-25T19:00:00-05:00"
                            >January 25, 1932—7 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>24. For your confidential information and guidance. Your 27, January 25, 9 a.m.,
                    second paragraph.</p>
                <p>When the Chinese Chargé stated that the Chinese Minister wished to know whether
                    American Government would be represented at the next meeting of the Council, the
                    Chief of the Division of Far Eastern Affairs replied that the question had not
                    been discussed and that he “had no doubt but that we would maintain a contact
                    but saw no reason to expect that we would have anyone sitting in or directly
                    associated with the meetings of the Council”.</p>
                <p>It is to be hoped that the Chinese Minister will not put forward the question of
                    American representation on the Council.<note n="51" xml:id="d74fn51">In telegram
                        No. 33, January 26, 9 a.m., the Consul at Geneva reported: “Yesterday
                        afternoon <persName corresp="#p_YWW1">Yen</persName> gave me oral assurances
                        that he would not raise the question of American representation on the
                        Council.” (793.94/3638)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_SHL1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
